saveRC(25.10)                                                    saveRC(25.10)

Name
       saveRC - Saves the RC extraction data in the specified directory

Syntax
       saveRC

       [-help]

       dirName

       Saves  the  RC  extraction data in the specified directory. Use the re-
       storeRC command to restore the parasitic data. Use this  command  after
       running either extractRC or spefIn to ensure that the parasitic data is
       available in Innovus database.

       Note:  You  can  restore the parasitic data on systems that are same as
       those used for saving the data. For example, if the data was  saved  on
       Linux in 32-bit mode, you can restore it on Linux 32-bit mode only.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for the saveRC parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man saveRC

       <dirName>
              Specifies the location of the RCDB directory. The directory name
              should follow the *.rcdb.d format.

Related Information
              * restoreRC

              * extractRC

              * spefIn

              * The following chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * RC Extraction

